This article is a press release from the White House announcing the establishment of the White House Council for Community Solutions. The council's mission is to support social innovation and civic participation by identifying effective community solutions, promoting cross-sector collaboration, highlighting best practices, and making recommendations to the President on engaging various stakeholders. The council will be composed of up to 30 members appointed by the President, with the Chair being designated by the President. The CNCS will provide funding and administrative support, and members of the council will serve without compensation. The council will terminate after two years, unless renewed by the President. The press release also includes general provisions stating that the order does not affect the authority of executive departments or create any enforceable rights or benefits.